## Frequently Asked Questions

### Is the Wallbox Pulsar Plus compatible with Intelligent Octopus?

No. The Wallbox Pulsar Plus does not support Intelligent Octopus or any other smart tariff integration. You can set manual charging schedules through the app, but the charger won't automatically optimise based on electricity prices. If smart tariff support is important to you, consider the [Ohme Home Pro](/reviews/ohme-home-pro-review/) instead.

### Does the Wallbox Pulsar Plus work with solar panels?

No. The Pulsar Plus has no solar integration capability. If you have solar panels and want to charge your EV using surplus solar energy, the [myenergi Zappi v2](/reviews/zappi-v2-review/) is the best option on the UK market.

### How long is the Wallbox Pulsar Plus warranty?

The Wallbox Pulsar Plus comes with a 2-year warranty — shorter than the 3-year warranty offered by most UK competitors including the Ohme Home Pro, Pod Point Solo 3, and myenergi Zappi.

### Is the Wallbox Pulsar Plus OZEV grant eligible?

Yes. The Wallbox Pulsar Plus is eligible for the UK government's OZEV grant, which covers up to £350 towards installation costs for renters, flat owners, and landlords. Homeowners who own their own property are not currently eligible.

### Can I use the Wallbox Pulsar Plus with any electric vehicle?

Yes. The Pulsar Plus uses the Type 2 connector, which is compatible with all EVs currently sold in the UK.

### Is Wallbox a reliable brand?

The Wallbox hardware is generally reliable, and most customers have no issues. However, the customer support — based in Barcelona — has received consistent criticism for slow response times and unresolved issues. This is worth factoring into your decision, particularly given the shorter 2-year warranty.

